<% content_for :home do %>
<div class="index_pane col-md-8 col-xs-12" >
  <div class="alert alert-info" class="page-header">
  <p>
    <h1>Report Before Blame</h1>
    <small>Discover the new way to report a problem to your development team elegant, simple and formal way.</small>

  </p>
  </br>
  <% if current_stakeholder %>
    <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="/reports" role="button">Let's Report</a>
  <% else %>
    <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="/stakeholders/sign_in" role="button">Sign in</a>
    <a class="btn btn-default btn-lg" href="/stakeholders/sign_up" role="button">Sign up</a>
  <% end %>

  </div>


  <div class="row">

    <div class="col-md-8">

        <%=image_tag("img1.png", class: "img-thumbnail")%>

        <div class="caption">
          </br>
          <h3>Be simple</h3>
          <p>Discover the new way to report a problem to your development team elegant, simple and formal way.<p><a href="#" class="btn btn-primary" role="button">Learn more</a> <a href="https://github.com/Maes95/ReportBeforeFlame" class="btn btn-default" role="button">GitHub</a></p>
        </div>

    </div>

    <div class="col-md-4">
        <div class="pane">
          <div class="row">
                <ul class="list-group">
                  <li class="list-group-item active"><h3>Be effective </h3></li>
                  <li class="list-group-item"> The aim of a bug report is to let the programmer see the failure itself.</li>
                  <li class="list-group-item"> Give them detailed instructions so that they themselves can make it fail. </li>
                  <li class="list-group-item"> It describes everything in detail what you saw and what you expected to see. Notes error messages .</li>
                  <li class="list-group-item"> Try to diagnose the problem yourself if you think you can , but if you do, also reported symptoms also .</li>
                  <li class="list-group-item"> Write clearly. Say what you mean, and make sure you can not misunderstand.</li>
                  <li class="list-group-item"> Be precise. Programmers like precision.</li>
                </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</br>

<footer class="alert alert-info"><small>2016 - Developed by Michel Maes</small></footer>
</div>




<% end %>
